35:30.671 --> 35:36.297
Well, until I got home, and I actually brought the 
94th Division artillery home. Oh, yeah, you

35:36.577 --> 35:38.079
brought it home with you. Brought it home, and we 
dispersed up at Camp Kilmer, New York, and... I

35:47.797 --> 35:50.880
always went scattered like a covered quail. Now, 
were you happy to get out of active duty, or did you

35:50.900 --> 35:58.028
think as a full colonel that maybe you might want to 
stay in the service? I had innumerable

35:59.170 --> 36:07.198
high-ranking good friends encourage me to stay in 
service. And as a full colonel, I could have done

36:09.461 --> 36:15.347
very well, I'm sure. On the other hand, the Army 
that I had seen up until that time was not conducive

36:18.998 --> 36:26.506
to the life I wanted to live. Meaning, I think in the 
first three years of our life in the Army, from

36:27.928 --> 36:48.870
December of 40, when I went in until I shipped 
overseas, I was moved 13

36:27.928 --> 36:48.870
or 14 times

36:51.955 --> 37:01.049
And of course, moving like that, you become a 
gypsy, meaning you don't have any place to plant

36:51.955 --> 37:01.049
your roots. Housing is hell around an army camp. 
And I didn't have enough seniority to get quarters

37:06.658 --> 37:13.609
on the post or being a new man. If I was a lieutenant 
colonel, I was still at the bottom of the totem pole

37:13.629 --> 37:20.359
because people ahead of me to get them. And we were 
living in rooms that, frankly, bear existence.

37:31.329 --> 37:45.305
And some places, Fort Meade, for instance, I got 
home on Saturday night every other week if there

37:31.329 --> 37:45.305
wasn't anything important going on. Otherwise, I 
skipped two more weeks.

37:52.874 --> 37:57.941
I couldn't project myself wanting that kind of 
life for 30 years. And I had the pressure put on me by

37:59.764 --> 38:05.692
a lot of high-ranking people to stay in. What a good 
life it would be and all that kind of business. On

38:10.259 --> 38:15.406
the other hand, I had a civil engineering 
education, and I wanted to get back and start

38:10.259 --> 38:15.406
making some money. And there's two ends of the 
pendulum. And I had to make a decision, and I

38:23.536 --> 38:33.729
decided to get out, stay in reserves, and stay

