And what were your functions as VXO? As the 
executive officer, I... I know what you do as the

40:32.735 --> 40:35.719
executive, but I mean, that wasn't a good 
question. I meant, what did the division do? It's a

40:38.462 --> 40:40.645
training division. Okay. In other words... 
Located here in Dallas? The headquarters is

40:44.050 --> 40:57.928
located here in Dallas, and they had a battalion in 
Amarillo and a battalion in College Station, a

40:44.050 --> 40:57.928
battalion in San Antonio, a battalion in 
Beaumont,

41:01.452 --> 41:02.673
Those poor battalions. And our function was to 
train the enlisted

41:03.854 --> 41:21.170
recruits to be proficient in their job as a 
reservist. Now, they could beat the draft by

41:22.071 --> 41:29.518
joining a reserve unit. That was an incentive to 
join a reserve unit, actually. And we took a man

41:34.259 --> 41:44.689
when he got to be 18 or just before he got drafted, 
he'd come join a reserve unit to beat it. They got an

41:45.169 --> 41:53.037
advance notice of a couple of weeks or something 
like that that they were going to be drafted on some

41:45.169 --> 41:53.037
date two weeks from now. And if they joined a unit 
while they didn't get drafted, the draft board

41:53.057 --> 41:56.400
would accept them. What did that mean for the 
quality of soldiers enlisted in the mountain?

42:01.818 --> 42:13.714
Well, of course, that was across the board at that 
time, meaning you got your share of high school

42:01.818 --> 42:13.714
dropouts, you got your share of high school 
students, you got your share of high school

42:01.818 --> 42:13.714
graduates, and you got your share of college 
graduates. Not graduates, but college students.

42:19.181 --> 42:23.687
So you got a cross-section of American life and... 
We had some mighty good men. Well, of course, some

42:26.536 --> 42:38.560
of them would be very good, but was there sort of a, 
if they're, part of the reason they're joining is

42:26.536 --> 42:38.560
to avoid the draft, were they in some respects 
anti-military? No, no, no, no, no, no. They

42:41.015 --> 42:50.846
weren't taking exemptions by claiming 4F, for 
instance, if they have physical disability or

42:41.015 --> 42:50.846
religious scruples or something like that. They 
wanted to continue their pursuit of education or

42:50.926 --> 42:56.332
their job or something. And the law said that they 
could join a reserve unit or National Guard and

42:57.113 --> 43:07.124
fulfill their military obligation. And so... 
they had the option of joining a reserve unit or

43:09.213 --> 43:13.379
being drafted. Now, the powerful incentive is to 
join a reserve unit, but some of them did, some of

43:14.821 --> 43:22.453
them didn't. But they made good soldiers. They 
eagerly learned, and it was a training mission for

43:23.935 --> 43:29.243
us. We went to active duty two weeks every year, 
