44:46.588 --> 44:52.535
set my heart and mind of making the 90th and Duvarty 
equal to any regular army unit. And I did. The first

44:55.739 --> 45:03.829
year, two of my four battalions passed the combat 
proficiency test. That was Colonel Coconose and

45:03.849 --> 45:07.594
Colonel Butler's battalion. Both of them became 
generals. That's right. And this is part of the

45:11.930 --> 45:13.732
reason why.

45:17.755 --> 45:18.776
That was the third year. The fourth year I was 
commander, three of the units passed. And my last

45:24.642 --> 45:38.374
year, all four of my units passed, which means my 
battalion could have been certified by a testing

45:24.642 --> 45:38.374
team, an army testing team, as proficient to go 
into combat. And that's the ultimate of training.

45:45.662 --> 45:52.331
General Rudder just told me I was pipe dreaming 
when I told him what my long-range plans were. But

45:53.513 --> 46:03.867
he couldn't have been more pleased when we passed 
with all four battalions my last year. And to me,

46:05.809 --> 46:07.011
that was... the ultimate of training.

46:13.287 --> 46:14.748
That's a real accomplishment. Really, it was. It 
